<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#871f78">Originally posted by Cinn on 09-08-2000 08:23 AM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">Bah!  If you're griping about the game, you shouldn't be playing!

Who says you need the best equipment to have fun?  Nobody need an ultra-rare GBS or jboots or SMR (can you tell I'm a caster? :P ) to have fun or see all Norrath.  I personally have only camped 2 times for my current character, who had nothing given to him for twinking, and was even item wiped at level 30.  I camped for jboots (about 3 hours total) and for my and a friend's shadowbound quests (about 6 hours total).  I made it to level 45, I had fun, and I've made lots of friends.  

My equipment, at first glance, sucks.  The best items I have are 7int,7str necklace, all the shadowbound quest stuff (robe, gloves, boots, and harvester), a sheer bone mask and dagger of marnek.  All the rest can easily, and fairly, be considered "crap."  However, I have an int of 195, have been in every dungeon in Norrath except the Hole and Sol B, and in half of the Kunark zones.

Nobody has to camp.  If you dont like it, dont do it.  Yes, you can DO a dungeon still.  My favorite example of this is Paw.  The mobs get harder as you go further in and the spawn is a relatively quick one (6 mins I think).  I cannot count the number of times a few friends and I started at the entrance and decided to see how far in we could get.  Once we were unable to advance (eithier by encountering too many gnolls, too high of a level gnolls, or those pesky necro and enchanter gnolls, we would either a)die, or b) call it a night and come back in a few more levels.

My biggest pet peeve is when people complain that when they die, they lose 4 hours or whatever amount of "work."  EQ IS NOT SUPPOSED TO BE WORK!  IF IT IS, DONT PLAY!  GET A (OR ANOTHER) JOB AND GET PAID FOR SO CALLED "WORK!"

Sorry about the ramblings and stream of thought writing, but had to get a few things of my chest.  :)</TEXTAREA>
</td></tr>
